76561198108028866,Recommended,227000,28779813,"Posted: 28 December, 2016",all,Daddy Flynn,"Primordia is a retro-styled point and click adventure game set in a dystopian future in which Man has gone extinct. Only machines remain, struggling to survive in the junk-filled wastelands. The protagonist will have to face many challenges in order to retrieve his source of power, gradually learning about the hidden thruth of his world along the way.The gameplay is very simple, as is every other adventure game: you'll have to explore, find and combine multiple items and use them at the right places to progress. What separates this game from the others is it's theme and its great humor. The last being delivered by a lovable sidekick who also serves the purpose of a hint bot. The puzzles are clever and challenging but not impossibly hard.The story is filled with rich and interesting lore, but is very linear (except at the very end, where you have multiple endings available). Each dialogue feels thought out and unique.The graphics are very reminiscent to those of Fallout 1: pixelated and low-resolution with dark brownish tones, which is tolerable since they seemed to be aiming for the retro theme. The only exception is the handful of brief cutscenes presenting very detailled close-ups of the action, which help with the immersion. The soundtrack is atmospheric and blends well with the setting. The voice acting is truely amazing.There's even some replayability value for those who wish try the commentary mode.So in short;for a 7 hour game with a good storyline and challenging puzzles paired with immersive soundtrack and great voice-acting, the pricetag is well worth the experience."
,Recommended,227000,28811648,"Posted: 29 December, 2016",all,Ocey,"Though perhaps not worth full price, this game is a gem that leaves you thinking about it long after it ends. The puzzles, for the most part, aren't too difficult, with a few exceptions that force you to pay very close attention to the lore. the pixel art is gorgoeus, though the map is perhaps a little small. The characters, though, are what make this game special. Much like Portal, these robots draw you in and force emotion upon you. Their witty banter and personalities are just so fresh and engaging. If you're looking for a game with nice graphics, a bit of thinking involved, and an awesome story with emotive characters, pick Primordia up on sale!"
