76561198144593917,Recommended,227000,20914220,"Posted: 2 February, 2016",all,mikesanerd,"I thought Primordia was a very good game, and I would recommend it both in terms of mechanics and story. I am a big fan of the Blackwell games, and this game has many of the same strengths.Pros:+ Excellent story. There's legitimately a lot to think about in this game, including political, religious, and social commentary. The game is set in a world where humans are extinct and only robots are left. We see how the society they create is a very clever mirror of our own, with plenty of parody of our own flaws along the way.+ The point and click puzzles are solid. They are somewhat difficult, but solvable without having to consult a walkthrough because the solutions make sense once you get them. To me, this is one of the most important things about gameplay in a point and click. You have to use your brain to solve the puzzles.+ If you do start struggling, you can get hints by talking to people (especially your sidekick Crispin), which again means you don't need to consult the internet to get a nudge in the right direction. Normally, he will give you a clue about which area you should be searching, or which object you should be fiddling with.+ The art and aesthetics in the game are good. The characters are interesting-looking, and the world is very neat.+ The game is paced well. It does a nice job of moving you from place to place, advancing the story and revealing the mysteries by steps.Cons:- Hard to think of any. I suppose the UI can be a bit clunky until you get used to it, especially how you access your inventory."
