,Recommended,227000,28997808,Posted: 3 January,all,ShaunzyBombzy,"This was an impulse buy while it was on the Steam winter sale, and it was one of the best impulse buys I've ever done.There is something truly unique and amazing about this game, and if you're reading this and wondering whether or not you should buy it, let me give you the rundown.Excellent:-The story is compelling, and populated with incredibly unique characters. One of my favorites is a fairly minor character that speaks in a religious cadence, and it's just such a cool little scene, it really stuck with me.-The characters are diverse and incredibly easy to become attached to. They are so well written, that you could name a character from hearing just a TINY snippet of their dialogue.-There are some truly genius puzzles here that absolutely blew me away.-The art is pretty breathtaking. The whole game feels alien and strange, but a familiar shadow seems to hang over it. It's just ♥♥♥♥ing great.Meh:-The voice acting for both Horatio and Crispin, the two main characters, is a little...off. Horatio I kind of got used to, and his monotone drone ended up being more part of his personality than anything, but Crispin has some pretty well-written lines that are delivered pretty awkwardly, and I found him pulling me back out of the game a little bit every so often. That being said, Crispin is delightful, if a tad annoying.-Some of the puzzles are absolutely rediculous, with some of them being outright pixelhunting. With as intelligent as the rest of the game is, it makes these puzzles even HARDER, because you expect the answer to make more sense. For instance (No spoilers here, don't worry.)There is a part of the game where your path is impeded, and the answer is the first thing that comes to your mind: ""Crispin should just move that."" And that is, indeed, the answer to that quandry.There's a part where you need to find an item, but you aren't told where it can be found or where to start. Had to resort to a walkthrough on this one, because the answer lay in a very cluttered, dark area of the screen. You never think ""This game will resort to pixel hunting"", because the rest of the game is just...too well thought out.So most of my complaints are ""Come on, Primordia, you're BETTER than this!"", which should absolutely tell you something. How this isn't a HUGELY known game is beyond me.In conclusion: Buy it, you son of a ♥♥♥♥♥."
