f this was a hidden-object-game. It´s hard to even recognize the textures and by looking closer you´ll get more confused than you already are. I bought this because I like point ´n click games a lot, and I have to admit that Primordia looked a lot better in the trailer. I wish the developers would have designed this more like Daedalic would have done, instead of Lucas Arts´ way, so that I could enjoy the game. The harder I try, the more I see how pointless it is. Playing such an awesome game is exhausting if you can´t clearly detect important elements.To not repeat me I will close this review now, if you read closely you should already have understood what I was saying. I  do seriously hope that you´ll have different experiences while playing Primordia."
