,Recommended,227000,11305060,"Posted: 18 July, 2014",all,１４０．８５,"This game surprised me. I went in expecting another tedious point-n-click, but was quickly sucked into the world that is Primoridia. You play a robot named Horatio that is on a quest for the rather simple goal of finding his home's battery. What ensues is a storyline that unveils a history and lore rooted in a mixture of ""God and his creation"", aiming forward with questions of freewill and the role of the State within a society. All the while, Horatio simply wants his power core.A brilliant, rich and enticing game. It asks more questions that it answers, while playing with your imagination and leaves you wanting more from this universe. All in all, if you're looking for a game that challenges your logic and problem-solving skills, while experiencing a well-developed world and excellent cast of characters, look no further."
,Recommended,227000,11344116,"Posted: 21 July, 2014",all,ranakanth,"Overall satisfying adventure game with only a few caveats.  Most of all I recommend this game.Pros:• Thought-provoking story full of moral ambiguities and juxtaposed viewpoints making you question your own judgments of the characters and their actions.• Good interface with a minimum of unnecessary clicking and waiting.• Varied endings dependant on choices made by the player.• Interesting scenery, good voice acting, and excellent atmosphereic soundtrack.Cons:• Completely unnecessary gender references at various points.  It's a world full of robots... Why does there need to be a ""female"" robot with boob-curves, or gender binary relationship references between androgynous mechanoids?• Serious tone somewhat undermined by numerous 4th-wall jokes by  a main character.• Lots of back-tracking and occasionally preposterous leaps in logic were needed to solve puzzles.  Several times I found myself resorting to ""randomly combine junk until something happens"" or having to look up walkthroughs, and being utterly baffled how someone would arrive at that solution.As stated above, I do highly recommend this game, and I enjoyed the story.  You should check it out!"
