76561198036186446,Recommended,227000,7651015,"Posted: 13 November, 2013",all,Ca_Putt,"Certainly one of the best point and click Adventures I've played since the nineties!* Both immersive and humerous. The story is Great and told extremely well. the art style is very appealing combining art nouveau and cyberpunk proves a valid design concept, the resolution ould be a tad bit higher tho and animations are a bit of a let down but that's a flaw of many games in the genre.Gameplay is fluid, controlls and leveldesign are sensible, avoiding frustration. Riddles range from realtively easy tasks to complex and hard enigmas, without lowering to the level of odd/alien/generic minigames or resulting in daylong meditations on what to do. Unlike most P&Cs with inventory, Primordias items are neither randomly taken from the environment(aka taking the banana instead of the wench) nor require absurd combinations, most ""crating"" tasks are sensible.The Help function is a bit wonky, it's hints range from being very specific to being nomore than a slight nudge in the right direction and there are no ""advice levels"" or ""search functions"". there is no hotspot highlighter, which may be seen both ways. You will have to think a bit to get this game done but it's very well solvable without any outside help** or random clicking.It's also fully*** voiced, and quite good if I may add.Ps: Unniic, Genius!*Probably THE best if you dismiss myst 4 as not a point and click game**I required it once, when I was standing infront of the hotspot. The hotspot was even named ""crystal""   -.-***The is one spot(info booth) where I would have liked an additional voiceover, something Myst 4 did: voice all written text."
