,Recommended,227000,875587,"Posted: 22 July, 2013",all,Jarylan,"Words cannot express the deep and thoughtful world that Primordia is. Unless for some reason, you hate – and I mean, truly, with burning fire, HATE – point and click adventure games, you owe it to yourself to play this game.As dark as the world can seem, humor abounds in this game. The simple graphics are still beautifully rendered, and the characters you meet are ones who will climb inside your head, and stay for the long haul. With a cast of incredibly well realized and acted robots, the world doesn't just invite you in; it sucks you down, and makes you a part of it. Things in this game will be thought about days, weeks later. Enough cannot be said for how immersive this game is.As unfortunate and bleak as the world of Primordia may seem, it has many things I wish to see again. Perhaps, if enough people play Primordia, some day we can all go back together."
